^B@2hondo717: Let us discuss how to bid over a 1N overcall. Since pard has opened already, it is a different situation for me than if terry had simply opened 1N. Here is the general rules about bidding over a 1N overcall. If you have 8 points or more, you should consider doubling the 1N overcall, because it is likely it will go down, often a lot. If you have a long suit and a weak hand, then you can bid your suit. You can also raise partner. The basic idea is, unlike normal auctions, where new suit by responder is forcing, over a 1N overcall, a new suit by responder is weak at the 2 level. It is just competing.|
